I am a video games programmer, currently based in South England. Over the past 5+ years I have specialised as an AI Programmer. Among various things that I've done, I designed, built and developed the AI technology for Codemasters' DiRT5 from the ground up and prior to that, I've worked on multiple racing titles at Codemasters. I also have extensive experience as an integrated tools programmer in C++ in UnrealEngine4. My primary interests are in the fields of artificial intelligence and procedural content generation.

Coming from a Computer Science/Mathematics background, I am knowledgeable of linear algebra, calculus and core computer science topics - skills which have proven to give a competitive advantage in the industry.

As a developer I have:

• Strong C++ programming skills;

• 5+ years of experience in the games industry;

• Experience in C#.NET (Silverlight) and Python;

• Experience developing on multiple platforms (PC, PS4, XBox One, PS2 Linux Kits);

• Designed, implemented and maintained various flexible gameplay systems. Worked closely with designers and programmers to ensure a great player experience;

• Mentored multiple graduate and mid-level engineers on positive programming practices and conventions;

• Experience in interviewing mid-level and graduate-level programming candidates. Developed a set of interviewing techniques and soft skills to evaluate the discrepancy between a candidate's presented ability vs their actual ability;

• Designed and implemented multiple integrated tools, iteratively, identifying and resolving content pipeline and tools usability issues with artists and designers;

• Working knowledge of programming best practices and object-oriented programming (MVC, some design patterns);

• Experience with asset creation packages, including 3DS Max, StructureSynth and MeshLab;

• Experience with third-party engines: Unity (pre-ECM) and UnrealEngine4 (pre-4.16);

• An understanding of and appreciation for milestones, schedules, deadlines, and efficient game development processes. 

• Working with task management systems: Jira and Trello;

• Experience writing technical documentation;

• Working with version control: Perforce and Plastic SCM;

